od to confirm we can discover configured ports. However, I've noticed challenges with native calls failing due to the empty library. So perhaps we should adjust our assertions to not check for actual ports and just confirm enumerations aren’t null or empty.\n6554:[thinking] I wonder if class initialization happens at runtime for gnu.io.CommPortIdentifier? If the test references a class, it might initialize when running, which means I need reflection metadata. Also, does System.loadLibrary function correctly in the native image runtime for an empty library? I’ll need to check the LD_LIBRARY_PATH and java.library.path environment variables.\n6562:[tool-call] delta {\"path\":\"tests/src/org.rxtx/rxtx/2.1.7/src/test/java/org_rxtx/rxtx/CommPortIdentifierTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_rxtx.rxtx;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport gnu.io.CommPortIdentifier;\\nimport java.util.Collections;\\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\\nimport java.util.List;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\npublic class CommPortIdentifierTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void getPortIdentifiersCreatesDriverAndReturnsEnumeration() {\\n        Enumeration<?> identifiers = CommPortIdentifier.getPortIdentifiers();\\n        List<?> discoveredIdentifiers = Collections.list(identifiers);\\n\\n        assertThat(discoveredIdentifiers)\\n                .allSatisfy(identifier -> assertThat(identifier).isInstanceOf(CommPortIdentifier.class));\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}\n6563:[tool-call] end id=call_emAtC9rlKaE5E96nFoNMP54v|fc_0e64ebe85c220c0a0169f270c3242481a1aeab5235e4075afc name=write args={\"path\": \"tests/src/org.rxtx/rxtx/2.1.7/src/test/java/org_rxtx/rxtx/CommPortIdentifierTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\