ate Feature class in the test source to avoid direct dependencies on JUnit? This is a bit tricky!\\n\\n**Adjusting test class dependencies**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how the Feature implementation is referenced in the test jar and image classpath. However, if there are no test annotations, JUnit might not load it. Since it references Feature, the native-image builder can handle it, but the JVM test may not. I need to set the dependency to testCompileOnly instead of testImplementation, which means moving the Feature implementation to a separate class. The rule about mapping dynamic report classes suggests that coverage should be maintained in its own test file. This could get complicated!\\n\\n**Evaluating build dependencies**\\n\\nI'm noticing that the test class no longer implements a specific feature, and it's tied to the dependency testCompileOnly. Keeping graal-sdk off the runtime/imagecp seems to be a goal here. But I wonder if compileOnly is missing from the nativeTestCompile classpath. It looks like the feature interface isn't included in the application classpath, but the builder module has it. Hopefully, everything should still work as intended.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0e64ebe85c220c0a0169f273d3abc881a1994c84718e9c325c\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp8nPksd-0lhx50jGDCwaMg8MAjf5wo_yJEgBBRgs97V5Be_uQkTN8gKBKsC9IEXFpKuilIPN--GOlXKqvLL4ecRTGfLUqI8jnFwBfxok6nhsMtnkpETNBAhnKSugdMWPuw40Jgm1NT1VbACTGIB4jvPrqZLHZMzOQQdsmAPbO2orNLMcA8MwyvFxOXkVsx43t6n6MK3tos1FDxvOM-aM4KxYNP4-PF_SJnNUh95GcUIW5XJrMw5oUMi4rgw7CMAXDxKM_dgst9MmjvOkbpNfxwcmvivc54GK2uwbp0SVNbqpdkbJnX_udrLZv_zO0HMe9yh9lnzAPNUADAR6PsGZAOVrSFrlxMy2SYlCNBoU4xKqjowbqx0_fLKWnGRtAY9OAXK55X3V9oMeMTPBfIku5WCCbWEjW8txStjmRtpEc2Ff4U5wPhlolIVzhsZOqhfZt3sJjAwbSCVMGtF56e3ttkoiJZ6RgksvEtAWRuhr0sqEyH9UB7UxSV9Twzxt3MHfvZ0yGjpBFXGwoWN_M6NS_7hcll5pwJFjAaYpiHISkIhn7slQOUujkBBAgMb5LOuhYQiJUXS4zmP_jpssKxazu1kscZaM3WCaoCGF52joDSxpCCIMmcXo7IwOf97E5QqICf8ut9UZ4R6mBdMgwB